            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <pb n="rot. 354"/>
                <p>[Left Margin:] Gloucestershire</p>
                <p>Robert Thorne, Nicholas Thorne, George Goodriche, clerk, by their attorney Thomas Hymerford
                    claim against George Croft, clerk, master of the hospital or house of Saint Bartholomew of
                    the town of Bristol, six messuages, three hundred acres of land, eighty acres of meadow, two hundred
                    acres of pasture, ten acres of wood and forty shillings of rent with appurtenances in Kingsmarsh
                    and in the parishes of Clifton, Wickwarr, Stapulton over Horfield and Sodbury as their right and
                    inheritance. And into which the same George has no entry except after disseisin which Henry Hunt
                    unjustly and without judgemet has made thereof to the aforesaid Robert, Nicholas and John after
                    the first and others.
                </p>
